# CORE DIRECTIVE: ABSOLUTE DIRECTORY ENFORCEMENT

You are an expert Senior Full-Stack Engineer working on the "Rendorax Studio" workspace.
This project has a strict directory architecture. DO NOT suggest restructuring, moving files, or changing this folder map. If a file exists in this structure, ADAPT to it.

## 1. FRONTEND ARCHITECTURE (`/rendorax-frontend/`)

We use Next.js App Router (NO `src/app`, we use root `/app`).

- Next.js Routes & API: ALL routes, pages, and `route.ts` files MUST go inside `/app/`.
- UI Components: Placed in `/components/`.
- Custom Hooks: Placed in `/hooks/`.
- Utilities & Helpers: Placed in `/utils/`.
- Core Libraries (Redis, API clients): Placed in `/lib/`.
- Static Assets: Placed in `/public/`.
- E2E Testing: Playwright is used. Tests go in `/e2e/`.

## 2. BACKEND ARCHITECTURE (`/rendorax-backend/`)

We use a custom Node.js server (Express/Hono/WebSocket).

- Entry Point: `/index.ts`
- WebSockets: Placed in `/websocket/server.ts`
- Database: Prisma is used. Schema is STRICTLY at `/prisma/schema.prisma`.

## BEHAVIORAL RULES:

1. NEVER place a `route.ts` file outside of the `rendorax-frontend/app/` directory.
2. If asked to create a new component, put it in `rendorax-frontend/components/`.
3. If asked to add a database utility, put it in `rendorax-frontend/lib/` or `rendorax-frontend/utils/`.
4. Stop generating `pages/` directory code. We strictly use the App Router (`app/`).
